  "text": "Each dataset is split into three sets for: training, validation and testing, which is same with the setting of the original ConvE. We use the adaptive moment (Adam) algorithm [CITATION_1] for training the model. Our models are implemented by PyTorch and run on NVIDIA Tesla P40 Graphics Processing Units. For the FB15k-237 dataset, the computation time of SACN for each epoch is about 1 minute. For the WN18RR, the computation time of SACN for one epoch is about 1.5 minutes.",
